<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Microsoft and OpenAI Loosen Their Partnership</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/27/technology/microsoft-openai-partnership.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/27/technology/microsoft-openai-partnership.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/27/technology/microsoft-openai-partnership.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Microsoft, OpenAI’s biggest financial partner, will continue to license the start-up’s technology but will no longer be its exclusive licensee.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz and Karen Weise</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 13:48:54 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Startup</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Microsoft</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/09/11/multimedia/27BIZ-MICROSOFT-OPENAI/11BIZ-OPENAI-1-qwbf-videoSixteenByNineJu