teenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>J.D. Biersdorfer</media:credit><media:description>The timer function in the phone’s clock app is just one of the many features to aid home chefs.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Here Are the Key Players in the OpenAI Trial</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/technology/key-players-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/technology/key-players-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/technology/key-players-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Elon Musk, Sam Altman and several other key artificial intelligence industry figures are slated to testify in the trial, which is expected to last several weeks.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 16:03:28 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">live-detached</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sam Altman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Yvonne Gonzalez Rogers</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Satya Nadella</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mira Murati</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Shivon Zillis</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Helen Toner</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tasha McCauley</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Ilya Sutskever</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/04/28/arts/28openai-trial-tech-whos-who/28openai-trial-tech-whos-who-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Eric Lee/The New York Times; Mike Kai Chen for The New York Times</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Elon Musk Assails Sam Altman on Social Media Before OpenAI Trial</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/technology/elon-musk-social-posts-sam-altman-openai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/technology/elon-musk-social-posts-sam-altman-openai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/technology/elon-musk-social-posts-sam-altman-openai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Mr. Musk’s posts on X have pushed his narrative that OpenAI has lost its way.</description><dc:creator>Ryan Mac</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 14:42:34 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">X</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sam Altman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/04/28/multimedia/28openai-trial-elontweets-lpzt/28openai-trial-elontweets-lpzt-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Kenny Holston/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Elon Musk on his phone during President Trump’s joint address to Congress at the U.S. Capitol last year.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>G.M.’s Profit Bolstered by a $500 Million Tariff Refund</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/business/general-motors-trump-tariffs.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/business/general-motors-trump-tariffs.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/28/business/general-motors-trump-tariffs.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Because of a February Supreme Court decision, General Motors said it would receive refunds on some of the tariffs it had paid.</description><dc:creator>Neal E. Boudette</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 15:07:25 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">International trade</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Rebates Refunds</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tariff</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">GM</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Supreme Court</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SCOTUS</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/04/28/multimedia/28biz-gm-earnings-gjvz/28biz-gm-earnings-gjvz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Brett Carlsen for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>A General Motors plant in Spring Hill, Tenn. The company is still affected by other tariffs — including those on imported steel, aluminum, cars and auto parts.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Paul Brainerd Dies at 78; Pioneered Desktop Publishing With PageMaker</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/21/technology/personaltech/paul-brainerd-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/21/technology/personaltech/paul-brainerd-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/21/technology/personaltech/paul-brainerd-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>His software brought printing into the digital age, allowing users to stop manually splicing columns of text and graphics and instead create layouts on a virtual pasteboard.</description><dc:creator>Michael S. Rosenwald</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 16:14:24 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Paul Brainerd</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Obituary</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Publishing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Software</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Desktop computer</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Printing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Word processor</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Aldus</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Adobe</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/03/23/multimedia/19Brainard-02-wmhq/19Brainard-02-wmhq-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600-v2.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>IslandWood</media:credit><media:description>Mr. Brainerd in an undated photo. After Aldus merged with Adobe Systems in 1994, he left the company and devoted the rest of his life to philanthropy, especially environmental conservation efforts in the Pacific Northwest.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Useful Local Travel Apps to Download Before You Go Abroad</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/19/travel/local-apps-international-travel.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/19/travel/local-apps-international-travel.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/19/travel/local-apps-international-travel.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Ride-hailing, dining and navigation apps you rely on at home may not be the best options in many countries. Here are local alternatives to download before you go.</description><dc:creator>Ruffin Prevost</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 09:02:31 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Travel</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tourism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">vacations</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mobile Apps</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Car Service</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Public Transit</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Reservations</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/name